  {

   "source": [
    "from fmdtools.analyze.common import setup_plot\n",
    "from mpl_toolkits.mplot3d import proj3d\n",
    "\n",
    "def plot_labs(labs, x, y, z, fig):\n",
    "    for i, label in enumerate(labs):\n",
    "            xlab, ylab, _ = proj3d.proj_transform(x[i], y[i], z[i],  ax.get_proj())\n",
    "            if label=='stuck_left':\n",
    "                xyt=(-20,-30)\n",
    "            elif label=='stuck':\n",
    "                xyt=(20,-30)\n",
    "            else:\n",
    "                xyt=(20,30)\n",
    "            plt.annotate(label, xy=(xlab, ylab), xytext=xyt, \n",
    "                textcoords='offset points', ha='center', va='bottom',\n",
    "                bbox=dict(boxstyle='round,pad=0.2', fc='white', alpha=1.0),\n",
    "                arrowprops=dict(arrowstyle='-|>', color=colors[2]))\n",
    "\n",
    "def plot_mode_space(faultdomain, size=30, alpha=0.5, label='', color='blue', marker='o', fig=None, ax=None, figsize=(4,4), show_labs=False):\n",
    "    x = []\n",
    "    y = []\n",
    "    z = []\n",
    "    labs = []\n",
    "    for faulttup, fault in faultdomain.faults.items():\n",
    "        dist_dict = dict(fault.disturbances)\n",
    "        x.append(dist_dict.get('s.friction', 0.0))\n",
    "        y.append(dist_dict.get('s.transfer', 1.0))\n",
    "        z.append(dist_dict.get('s.drift', 0.0))\n",
    "        labs.append(faulttup[1])\n",
    "\n",
    "    fig, ax = setup_plot(fig=fig, ax=ax, figsize=figsize, z=True)\n",
    "    ax.scatter(x, y, z, s=size, alpha=alpha, color=color, label=label, marker=marker)\n",
    "    if show_labs:\n",
    "        plot_labs(labs, x, y, z, fig)  \n",
    "    return fig, ax"
   ]
  },

  {
   "cell_type": "code",

   "source": [
    "def add_layer(fig, ax):\n",
    "    proj=ax.get_tightbbox(fig.canvas.get_renderer())\n",
    "    \n",
    "    ax2 = fig.add_subplot(projection='3d')\n",
    "    ax2.patch.set_alpha(0.0)\n",
    "    xmin, ymin, zmin = proj3d.proj_transform(ax.get_xlim()[0], ax.get_ylim()[0], ax.get_zlim()[0],  ax.get_proj())\n",
    "    xmax, ymax, zmax = proj3d.proj_transform(ax.get_xlim()[1], ax.get_ylim()[1], ax.get_zlim()[1],  ax.get_proj())\n",
    "    ax2.set_xlim(xmin, xmax)\n",
    "    ax2.set_ylim(ymin, ymax)\n",
    "    ax2.set_zlim(zmin, zmax)\n",
    "    plt.axis('off')\n",
    "    return ax2\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "def plot_mode_spaces(fd_range, fd_set, fd_id, title=\"Space of Fault Modes\"):\n",
    "    fig, ax = plot_mode_space(fd_range, label='range', color='goldenrod', size=5, alpha=0.25)\n",
    "    fig, ax = plot_mode_space(fd_set, color='magenta', alpha=0.25, label='set', size=30, fig=fig, ax=ax)\n",
    "    fig, ax = plot_mode_space(fd_id, color='blue', alpha=1.0, label='set', size=30, marker='x', fig=fig, ax=ax)\n",
    "    ax.scatter([0], [1], [0], label=\"nominal\", marker=\"*\", s=50)\n",
    "    ax2 = add_layer(fig, ax)\n",
    "    fig, ax2 = plot_mode_space(fd_id, color='blue', alpha=1.0, label='set', size=30, show_labs=True, marker='x', fig=fig, ax=ax2)\n",
    "    \n",
    "    ax.set_title(title)\n",
    "\n",
    "    ax.set_xlabel('friction')\n",
    "    ax.set_ylabel('transfer')\n",
    "    ax.set_zlabel('drift')\n",
    "    ax.legend()\n",
    "    return fig, ax"
   ]
  },

  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 37,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "from sklearn.cluster import DBSCAN as cluster #DBSCAN\n",
    "import numpy as np"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 40,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def get_X(mdlhists, hmode = True):\n",
    "    x = np.array([[value[-1]] for scen, value in mdlhists.get_values('flows.pos.s.x').items()])\n",
    "    y = np.array([[value[-1]] for scen, value in mdlhists.get_values('flows.pos.s.y').items()])\n",
    "    return np.concatenate((x, y), axis=1)\n",
    "    "
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "To find similar trajectories, we will cluster on the x-y coordinates of the end position of the Rover accross these scenarios:"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 62,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "X_range = get_X (mdlhists_range)\n",
    "ec_range = [endclass for scen, endclass in results_range.get_values('end_dist').items() if scen[0:6]!='nominal']"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 63,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "X_set = get_X (mdlhists_set)\n",
    "ec_set = [endclass for scen, endclass in results_set.get_values('end_dist').items() if scen[0:6]!='nominal']"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 76,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "X_id = get_X (mdlhists_id, hmode = False)\n",
    "ec_id = [endclass for scen, endclass in results_id.get_values('end_dist').items() if scen[0:6]!='nominal']\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "To identify where all the clusters are accross all three approaches, we first have to combine the three sets of data into one (otherwise it might cluster differently)."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 77,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "X = np.concatenate((X_range, X_set, X_id))"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "This runs the clustering algorithm:"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 78,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "cl = cluster().fit(X)\n",
    "labels = cl.labels_"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "The number of clusters is:"

  },

   "source": [
    "This function categorizes the results of each approach into the given clusters"
   ]

  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 89,
   "metadata": {},

   "source": [
    "def get_cats(categorizations, X, ec, unique_categorizations):\n",
    "    cats={}\n",
    "    for cat in unique_categorizations:\n",
    "        cats[cat] = [ec[i] for i, x in enumerate(X) if categorizations[tuple(x)]==cat]+[0]\n",
    "    return cats"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 90,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "cats = get_cats(categorizations, X_range, ec_range, unique_labels)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 91,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def worst_cat(categorizations, X, ec, unique_categorizations):\n",
    "    worst_cats={}\n",
    "    for cat in unique_categorizations:\n",
    "        cats = [ec[i] for i,x in enumerate(X) if categorizations[tuple(x)]==cat]+[0]\n",
    "        worst_cats[cat] = np.max(cats)\n",
    "    return worst_cats"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 92,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "worst_cat_id = worst_cat(categorizations,X_id, ec_id, unique_labels)\n",
    "worst_cat_range = worst_cat(categorizations,X_range, ec_range, unique_labels)\n",
    "worst_cat_set = worst_cat(categorizations,X_set, ec_set, unique_labels)"
   ]

   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Finally, we use the following to calculate more detailed statistics about the cluster coverage."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 101,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def calc_2d_cov_loss(xmin, xmax, ymin, ymax, xs, ys):\n",
    "    return calc_coverage_loss(xmin, xmax, xs)*calc_coverage_loss(ymin, ymax, ys)\n",
    "def calc_coverage_loss(xmin, xmax, xs):\n",
    "    if xs:\n",
    "        return (xmax-np.max(xs)+np.min(xs)-xmin)/(xmax-xmin)\n",
    "    else: \n",
    "        return  (xmax-xmin)/(xmax-xmin)\n",
    "def get_xs_ys(values, X_type):\n",
    "    return [v[0] for v in values if v in X_type], [v[1] for v in values if v in X_type]"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 102,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "cov_loss_id,cov_loss_set,cov_loss_range = [],[],[]\n",
    "num_scens_id,num_scens_set,num_scens_range = [],[],[]\n",
    "for cat, values in cat_values.items():\n",
    "    xs = [v[0] for v in values]\n",
    "    ys = [v[1] for v in values]\n",
    "    xs_id, ys_id = get_xs_ys(values, X_id)\n",
    "    xs_set, ys_set = get_xs_ys(values, X_set)\n",
    "    xs_range, ys_range = get_xs_ys(values, X_range)\n",
    "    xmin,xmax,ymin,ymax = np.min(xs), np.max(xs), np.min(ys), np.max(ys)\n",
    "    \n",
    "    cov_loss_id.append(calc_2d_cov_loss(xmin,xmax,ymin,ymax ,xs_id,ys_id))\n",
    "    cov_loss_set.append(calc_2d_cov_loss(xmin,xmax,ymin,ymax ,xs_set,ys_set))\n",
    "    cov_loss_range.append(calc_2d_cov_loss(xmin,xmax,ymin,ymax, xs_range,ys_range))\n",
    "    \n",
    "    num_scens_id.append(len(xs_id));num_scens_set.append(len(xs_set));num_scens_range.append(len(xs_range))"
   ]
  },
